{"id":14881072,"mediaExerciseId":"60fc1d34-054a-4406-b757-b235371b0437","exerciseName":"23","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":235,"solutions":[{"id":6014619,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we should determine the clear price by using the invoice price and the coupon rate.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/af92a4d9f5c81ab6d022667a04f47d38/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/af92a4d9f5c81ab6d022667a04f47d38/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The clean price is the bond price without including any interest within. On the contrary, a dirty price is a price that contains accumulated interest. If we subtract the clean price from the dirty price, we will get the amount of the collected interest.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/0ac620530b5c5a33543479b3fce388fe/lateximg_large.png","width":999},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/0ac620530b5c5a33543479b3fce388fe/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We should first calculate the value of the accrued interest. Let's consider that the year has 360 days. Because the coupon payments are semiannual, one payout is for 180 days. We have four months left until the next payout. It is 120 days. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/06a88d75301f0312eeccced103c7c2c6/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/06a88d75301f0312eeccced103c7c2c6/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The accrued interest we should calculate for the days that passed (60 days). Let's calculate it by using the following formula. The par value of the bond is not written. Let's assume it is \\$1,000.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{accrued interest}&=\\text{par value}\\times\\dfrac{\\text{annual interest}}{2}\\times\\dfrac{60}{180}\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$1,000\\times\\dfrac{5.9\\%}{2}\\times0.333\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$9.833}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe accrued interest is \\$9.833.\n\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":459,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/6db52253f6c75fc53d1076def3d35845/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":231,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/6db52253f6c75fc53d1076def3d35845/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"To get the clean price, we should subtract the calculated accrued interest from the amount that we paid for the bond.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{clean price}&=\\$948-\\$9.833\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$938.167}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The clean price of the bond is \\$938.167.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":283,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/7749549484205e9abcea5623bd3b600f/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/6d870737866736c8ad602c8332a1d1b8/7749549484205e9abcea5623bd3b600f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"0b19847e-4408-4686-968b-8396c1007b7d","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881073,"exerciseName":"24","page":235,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"9c5c62f4-30bc-41bd-bf90-d45d71ebca1d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-24-9c5c62f4-30bc-41bd-bf90-d45d71ebca1d"},{"id":14881074,"exerciseName":"25","page":235,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1e682aab-a47e-4ace-add1-0aee4fa52cda","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-25-1e682aab-a47e-4ace-add1-0aee4fa52cda"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881071,"exerciseName":"22","page":235,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"e41a3590-f360-485e-b9aa-5741dfa8cea8","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-22-e41a3590-f360-485e-b9aa-5741dfa8cea8"},{"id":14881070,"exercis